name: laryngeal carcinoma
definition: A larynx cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells. [url:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carcinoma]

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, ME22S inhibited cell migration, invasion, and proliferation of human laryngeal carcinoma cell lines in culture and inhibited tumor growth in laryngeal carcinoma xenograft models (PMID: 26812910).

references.title: The Dual Inhibition of Met and EGFR by ME22S, a Novel Met/EGFR Bispecific Monoclonal Antibody, Suppresses the Proliferation and Invasion of Laryngeal Cancer.
